column6: The communication has been lost between the axis computer and the serial measurement board on measurement link 1 in drive module 1.
column7: This may be caused by bad connections or cables (screening), especially if non-ABB cables are used for additional axes. Possible causes are also faulty serial measurement board or axis computer.
column8: 1) Reset the robot's revolution counters as detailed in the robot Product Manual. 2) Make sure the cable between serial measurement board and axis computer is connected correctly, and that it meets the specification set by ABB. 3) Make sure the cable screen is correctly connected at both ends. 4) Make sure no extreme levels of electromagnetic interference are emitted close to the robot cabling. 5) Make sure the serial measurement board and axis computer are fully functional. Replace any faulty unit.
